ISI said it can withdraw from the merger agreement with Memotec if a better bid surfaces .
CMS Energy Corp. , Jackson , Mich. , said it has resumed the purchase of its common stock under a program approved by its directors in 1987 .
At the time of the original announcement , CMS said its board authorized the purchase of as many as five million of its shares .
A spokesman said 2.6 million shares have been purchased since then .
The company said it will buy additional shares `` from time to time in the open market or in private transactions at prevailing market prices . ''
